cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is about an intrusion detection system (IDS) that uses machine learning techniques, specifically autoencoder neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cascading two detectors, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
